(56, 1, '2014-09-12 16:07:09', '2014-09-12 16:07:09', '<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden">\r\n<div class="field-items">\r\n<div class="field-item even">\r\n<h3>1. Meteos- 57.9% (963 Votes)</h3>\r\n<a href="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/Meteos%20%282%20of%207%29_0.jpg?itok=U58sM7jU"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/Meteos%20%282%20of%207%29_0.jpg?itok=U58sM7jU" alt="" width="700" height="315" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LCS Elise Stats:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Games Played</em>: 5</li>\r\n	<li><em>Games Won</em>: 3</li>\r\n	<li><em>Win Rate</em>: 60%</li>\r\n	<li><em>Average KDA:</em> 6.1</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> apply red buff with an auto attack before going for a stun to make it easier to hit\r\n\r\n— Will Hartman (@meteoslol) <a href="https://twitter.com/meteoslol/statuses/504463837987614720">August 27, 2014</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>  While there are champions that can be successful without them, some kind of gap close or cc makes early game pressure and ganks much easier. Missing skill shots on a gank can end up wasting valuable jungle clearing time. Elise''s cocoon can be very difficult to hit if the teammate you''re ganking for doesn''t have some kind of reliable cc, so try to auto attack with red buff to make it a bit easier for yourself.  \r\n\r\n<h3>2. Shook - 15.8% (262 Votes)</h3>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/shookface.jpg?itok=KDjDsPXf"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/shookface.jpg?itok=KDjDsPXf" alt="" width="700" height="315" /></a>   <strong>LCS Elise Stats:</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Games Played</em>:9</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Games Won</em>: 7</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Win Rate</em>: 77.8%</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Average KDA</em>: 2.9</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<center></center>\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none">\r\n<a href="https://twitter.com/lolesports">@lolesports</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> When ganking just apply redbuff and use your damaging abbilities, hold on to your cocoon until they flash. — Shook (@ShookLoL) <a href="https://twitter.com/ShookLoL/statuses/504778852149649408">August 27, 2014</a>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nShook reinforces what Meteos told us, because even the pros know that it''s easy to miss a cocoon. The red buff slow will also make it easier for your laners to hit any cc they have, like a Thresh hook or a Nami bubble.\r\n<h3>Community Tips</h3>\r\nThis week, we got some bonus tips from a few more pro players and some more great advice from members of the community!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/meteoslol">@meteoslol</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> cocoon flash is a nice way to hit an unexpected stun. channel your cocoon and then cancel the animation with flash\r\n\r\n— I Will Dominate (@CrsDominate) <a href="https://twitter.com/CrsDominate/statuses/504469712701779968">August 27, 2014</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>  There was a little debate on Twitter around this one so I tested this myself just to be sure (not that I don''t trust you, Dom). Using Flash immediately after casting cocoon cancels the channeling animation and casts the cocoon instantly from the final location of the Flash. This means less time for the enemy to react and a higher chance of hitting them.  \r\n<center></center>\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none">\r\n<a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> Starting off tower dives is great on Elise. She can tank 2-3 shots and then repel in order to reset tower Aggro. — TomsGG (@SomePlatDude) <a href="https://twitter.com/SomePlatDude/statuses/504877341772742656">August 28, 2014</a>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWhile diving turrets can be dangerous, especially in the early game, it’s also a great way to snowball your lanes. As SomePlatDude points out, Elise is great at initiating since she can so easily get out of tower aggro range.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/CrsDominate">@CrsDominate</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/meteoslol">@meteoslol</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> Using your spider form Q to close in distance when chasing through a creep wave. Small but noticable\r\n\r\n— Ram Djemal (@BrokenshardEUW) <a href="https://twitter.com/BrokenshardEUW/statuses/504472221294014464">August 27, 2014</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEven though I''m sure none of us have <em>ever</em> missed Elise''s stun, Brokenshard offers a great tip for chasing down enemies. If you''ve got fast enough fingers, you can also use this tip as a way to get in position for a better chance at landing the stun in the first place.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'LCS Pro Tips: Elise', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '48-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-12 16:07:09', '2014-09-12 16:07:09', '', 48, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=56', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(57, 1, '2014-09-12 16:11:36', '2014-09-12 16:11:36', '<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden">\r\n<div class="field-items">\r\n<div class="field-item even"><center><strong><a href="/articles/lcs-pro-tips-elise" target="_blank">Remember to vote for next week''s champion, Elise!</a></strong></center>\r\n<h3>1. Balls- 59.0% (532 Votes)</h3>\r\n<a href="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/d1f1037c67.jpg?itok=gZ-AtpPY"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/d1f1037c67.jpg?itok=gZ-AtpPY" alt="" width="700" height="315" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LCS Renekton Stats:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Games Played</em>: 5</li>\r\n	<li><em>Games Won</em>: 2</li>\r\n	<li><em>Win Rate</em>: 40%</li>\r\n	<li><em>Average KDA:</em> 3.9</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<center>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/CrsQuas">@CrsQuas</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/SKfredy122">@SKfredy122</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/Cloud9gg">@Cloud9gg</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/TeamCurseGaming">@TeamCurseGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/SKGaming">@SKGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/lolesports">@lolesports</a> If you are behind don''t build tiamat and go full tank!\r\n\r\n— An Le (@C9Balls) <a href="https://twitter.com/C9Balls/statuses/502234746517487616">August 20, 2014</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</center>\r\nIt''s often tempting to get set into a certain build order, but it''s important to adapt to the situation. If you''re losing lane, building damage won''t often help you turn the tide since your opponent will just be buying more. As Balls says here, going tanky will usually be the most helpful to your team.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Fredy112 - 13.2% (119 Votes)</h3>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/b4976bb7ff.jpg?itok=XUmLyipQ"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/b4976bb7ff.jpg?itok=XUmLyipQ" alt="" width="700" height="315" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LCS Renekton Stats:</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Games Played</em>:8</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Games Won</em>: 6</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Win Rate</em>: 80%</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Average KDA</em>: 3.2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<center>\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none">\r\n<a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/C9Balls">@C9Balls</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/CrsQuas">@CrsQuas</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/Cloud9gg">@Cloud9gg</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/TeamCurseGaming">@TeamCurseGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/SKGaming">@SKGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/lolesports">@lolesports</a> push lane and play aggressive, create pressure in lane phase.\r\n\r\n— Simon Payne (@SKfredy122) <a href="https://twitter.com/SKfredy122/statuses/502424810224631808">August 21, 2014</a>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</center>If you''re used to more defensive top laners, Renekton might be a bit of a difficult transition. As Fredy points out, pushing and bullying during the laning phase is the best way to maintain an advantage. <em>As long as you have wards</em>, you should be able to safely play forward thanks to the added escape from slice and dice.\r\n<h3>3. Quas- 11.3% (102 Votes)</h3>\r\n<a href="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/3bd75b67ea.jpg?itok=kcBpcq-z"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/3bd75b67ea.jpg?itok=kcBpcq-z" alt="" width="700" height="315" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LCS Renekton Stats:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Games Played</em>:5</li>\r\n	<li><em>Games Won</em>: 2</li>\r\n	<li><em>Win Rate</em>: 40%</li>\r\n	<li><em>Average KDA</em>: 3.7</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<center>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/C9Balls">@C9Balls</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/SKfredy122">@SKfredy122</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/Cloud9gg">@Cloud9gg</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/TeamCurseGaming">@TeamCurseGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/SKGaming">@SKGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/lolesports">@lolesports</a> make sure you use your fury on ur Q when fighting in lane\r\n\r\n— Diego Ruiz (@CrsQuas) <a href="https://twitter.com/CrsQuas/statuses/502246153812209664">August 21, 2014</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</center>\r\nQuas'' tip is about fury management, one of the more difficult aspects of playing Renekton. Using the empowered spell on your Q during trades can greatly increase your damage (as seconded by <a href="https://twitter.com/RiotScarizard/status/502167363391729664" target="_blank">Scarizard the Gator Lord</a>).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h3>Community Tips</h3>\r\n\r\nCheck out some of the best tips from the community!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<center>\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none">\r\n<a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> To escape ganks, slice into the ganking opponent from river and then dice. This effectively takes your lane out of the fight.\r\n\r\n— Dylan Hornibrook (@CoC_Pepitas) <a href="https://twitter.com/CoC_Pepitas/statuses/502170158807646209">August 20, 2014</a>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</center>Dylan Hornibrook gives a great tip for escaping from ganks. Usually when a jungler shows up, the first instinct is to run straight to your tower. This is often effective, but jumping at the enemy jungler can actually take you further away from danger if you catch him while he''s still in the river.\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> All of his abilities reset his auto attack timer, so weave attacks between uses when going all in for maximum damage\r\n\r\n— DeClawd (@DeClawd) <a href="https://twitter.com/DeClawd/statuses/502167060596932609">August 20, 2014</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</center>DeClawd''s tip focuses on sustained damage in trades and engages. By using your spells to reset autos and auto attacking in between each, you can get much more burst damage. Particularly early on in the laning phase, this can swing trades your way and push the enemy out of lane.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'LCS Pro Tips: Renekton', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'lcs-pro-tips-renekton', '', '', '2014-09-15 11:07:33', '2014-09-15 11:07:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=57', 0, 'page', '', 0),
