(157, 1, '2014-09-29 11:16:31', '2014-09-29 11:16:31', '<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden">\r\n<div class="field-items">\r\n<div class="field-item even">\r\n\r\nLooking to deliver an Icathian Surprise to your lane opponents? Kog''Maw is your...monster. With a 2010 release date, this 4 year old void puppy has been around the rift a few times. During those years, he has cycled in and out of professional play and solo queue popularity.\r\n\r\nWe had a few top voted players who couldn''t respond this week due to preparation for Regionals and other conflicts. As a result, Doublelift and WildTurtle couldn''t be included this week. Since we only have two tips from pros this week, we took a few more of the best from the community. Have your own Kog tips? Share them in the comments down below!\r\n<h3>1. Imaqtpie - 12.2% (281 Votes)</h3>\r\n<a href="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/28f952aebb_0.jpg?itok=-hvXyxuC"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/28f952aebb_0.jpg?itok=-hvXyxuC" alt="" width="700" height="315" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LCS Kog''Maw Stats:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Games Played</em>: 3</li>\r\n	<li><em>Games Won</em>: 1</li>\r\n	<li><em>Win Rate</em>: 33.3%</li>\r\n	<li><em>Average KDA:</em> 5.7</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/lolesports">@lolesports</a> activate your w on imitations, once w runs out make sure to run in and die so you can also get your passive hit! :))\r\n\r\n— Michael Santana (@dignitasQtpie) <a href="https://twitter.com/dignitasQtpie/statuses/499738680903606272">August 14, 2014</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\nImaqtpie did respond with his tip...but did so in the classic qt style (ヽ༼ຈل͜ຈ༽ﾉ raise your dongers ヽ༼ຈل͜ຈ༽ﾉ). This tip might not be the most helpful for upping your Kog''Maw game, but hopefully it''s good for a laugh. I''m not sure what ''imitations'' are, but clearly they should be destroyed immediately. Get those Shaco clones. On a slightly more serious note, Icathian Surprise can be a great way to turn around a fight that doesn''t go your way. If you''re losing a close trade, you should do your best to slow them with E right before you die to increase your chances of landing the explosion to finish them off. It''s meant to be a last ditch effort, so I wouldn''t plan on using it in a trade as qt jokes, but definitely try to make the most of it in skirmishes and teamfights where you''re already going to die.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h3>2. CandyPanda- 11.0% (254 Votes)</h3>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/7d900ea1bb.jpg?itok=7mw5qBqu"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://na.lolesports.com/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/7d900ea1bb.jpg?itok=7mw5qBqu" alt="" width="700" height="315" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LCS Kog''Maw Stats:</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Games Played</em>:6</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Games Won</em>: 3</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Win Rate</em>: 50%</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Average KDA</em>: 3.5</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<center></center>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none">\r\n<a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/lolesports">@lolesports</a> Never use W to farm unless you''re forced to, instead force trades with e+w and zone\r\n\r\n— Adrian Pander (@CandyPandalol) <a href="https://twitter.com/CandyPandalol/statuses/499753838090682370">August 14, 2014</a>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLuckily, CandyPanda came through with a solid tip about using Kog''Maw''s W. Because of the bonus range and damage that it offers, using it to farm can be tempting, but ultimately this will hurt you in trades if it''s on cooldown. Saving it for trades paired with the huge slow from your E will make sure that you have an easier time bullying your lane opponent. TSM''s WildTurtle <a href="https://twitter.com/TSMWildTurtle/status/499620157581709312" target="_blank">hinted at the same thing</a>, but we ran out of time to get him to elaborate. Both focus on the fact that your W is one of your strongest damage outputs, so use the bonus hits on champions in lane or teamfights, and use the range to help you stay at a safer distance.\r\n<h3>Community Tips</h3>\r\nWe had a lot of great tips this week, and I decided to add a few bonus tips to make up for the lighter pro input.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> Make sure to combo your Bio-Arcane Barrage with your Caustic Spittle to get extra damage due to the armor/mr shred.\r\n\r\n— Chris Kindell (@chaotrix100) <a href="https://twitter.com/chaotrix100/statuses/500018010498039808">August 14, 2014</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\nChris Kindell brings up the important point that Kog''Maw''s Q has a significant armor and magic resist reduction (12-18% based on level), and leading with it before an engagement can really ramp up your damage.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<center></center>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none">\r\n<a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@riotkatana</a> When last-hitting under tower, you can set up last hits on the caster minions by using E on them; E + tower + auto = CS success\r\n\r\n— Kriz Cuenco (@ggcKrizzly) <a href="https://twitter.com/ggcKrizzly/statuses/500018479748362240">August 14, 2014</a>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLast hitting under tower can be extremely challenging - even pros miss minions in the early game when their AD is still too low to one-shot them. Kriz Cuenco''s tip is a great way to make your last hits more reliable without having to pop your W.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> Use your E + Q to get minions that you can''t auto instead of using your W for the range. It saves the cd and means you can trade\r\n\r\n— Phy (@thephylol) <a href="https://twitter.com/thephylol/statuses/500019093626712064">August 14, 2014</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPhy''s tip follows in the same vein, though it''s more of a general laning practice than exclusively an under tower situation. The recurring theme throughout all these tips is to save your W!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'LCS Pro Tips: Kog''Maw', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '62-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-29 11:16:31', '2014-09-29 11:16:31', '', 62, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=157', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(158, 1, '2014-09-29 11:21:03', '2014-09-29 11:21:03', '<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden">\n<div class="field-items">\n<div class="field-item even">\n<h3>1. Balls- 59.0% (532 Votes)</h3>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>LCS Renekton Stats:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><em>Games Played</em>: 5</li>\n	<li><em>Games Won</em>: 2</li>\n	<li><em>Win Rate</em>: 40%</li>\n	<li><em>Average KDA:</em> 3.9</li>\n</ul>\n<center>\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/CrsQuas">@CrsQuas</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/SKfredy122">@SKfredy122</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/Cloud9gg">@Cloud9gg</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/TeamCurseGaming">@TeamCurseGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/SKGaming">@SKGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/lolesports">@lolesports</a> If you are behind don''t build tiamat and go full tank!\n\n— An Le (@C9Balls) <a href="https://twitter.com/C9Balls/statuses/502234746517487616">August 20, 2014</a></blockquote>\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\n&nbsp;\n</center>\nIt''s often tempting to get set into a certain build order, but it''s important to adapt to the situation. If you''re losing lane, building damage won''t often help you turn the tide since your opponent will just be buying more. As Balls says here, going tanky will usually be the most helpful to your team.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<h3>2. Fredy112 - 13.2% (119 Votes)</h3>\n\n<img src="/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/b4976bb7ff.jpg?itok=XUmLyipQ" alt="" />\n\n<strong>LCS Renekton Stats:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<ul>\n	<li><em>Games Played</em>:8</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul>\n	<li><em>Games Won</em>: 6</li>\n</ul>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul>\n	<li><em>Win Rate</em>: 80%</li>\n</ul>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul>\n	<li><em>Average KDA</em>: 3.2</li>\n</ul>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<center>\n\n\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none">\n<a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/C9Balls">@C9Balls</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/CrsQuas">@CrsQuas</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/Cloud9gg">@Cloud9gg</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/TeamCurseGaming">@TeamCurseGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/SKGaming">@SKGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/lolesports">@lolesports</a> push lane and play aggressive, create pressure in lane phase.\n\n— Simon Payne (@SKfredy122) <a href="https://twitter.com/SKfredy122/statuses/502424810224631808">August 21, 2014</a>\n</blockquote>\n\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</center>If you''re used to more defensive top laners, Renekton might be a bit of a difficult transition. As Fredy points out, pushing and bullying during the laning phase is the best way to maintain an advantage. <em>As long as you have wards</em>, you should be able to safely play forward thanks to the added escape from slice and dice.\n<h3>3. Quas- 11.3% (102 Votes)</h3>\n<img src="/sites/default/files/styles/article_image/public/3bd75b67ea.jpg?itok=kcBpcq-z" alt="" />\n\n<strong>LCS Renekton Stats:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><em>Games Played</em>:5</li>\n	<li><em>Games Won</em>: 2</li>\n	<li><em>Win Rate</em>: 40%</li>\n	<li><em>Average KDA</em>: 3.7</li>\n</ul>\n<center>\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/C9Balls">@C9Balls</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/SKfredy122">@SKfredy122</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/Cloud9gg">@Cloud9gg</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/TeamCurseGaming">@TeamCurseGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/SKGaming">@SKGaming</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/lolesports">@lolesports</a> make sure you use your fury on ur Q when fighting in lane\n\n— Diego Ruiz (@CrsQuas) <a href="https://twitter.com/CrsQuas/statuses/502246153812209664">August 21, 2014</a></blockquote>\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\n&nbsp;\n</center>\nQuas'' tip is about fury management, one of the more difficult aspects of playing Renekton. Using the empowered spell on your Q during trades can greatly increase your damage (as seconded by <a href="https://twitter.com/RiotScarizard/status/502167363391729664" target="_blank">Scarizard the Gator Lord</a>).\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<h3>Community Tips</h3>\n\nCheck out some of the best tips from the community!\n\n&nbsp;\n<center>\n\n\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none">\n<a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> To escape ganks, slice into the ganking opponent from river and then dice. This effectively takes your lane out of the fight.\n\n— Dylan Hornibrook (@CoC_Pepitas) <a href="https://twitter.com/CoC_Pepitas/statuses/502170158807646209">August 20, 2014</a>\n</blockquote>\n\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</center>Dylan Hornibrook gives a great tip for escaping from ganks. Usually when a jungler shows up, the first instinct is to run straight to your tower. This is often effective, but jumping at the enemy jungler can actually take you further away from danger if you catch him while he''s still in the river.\n\n<center>\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en" xml:lang="en" data-conversation="none"><a href="https://twitter.com/RiotKatana">@RiotKatana</a> All of his abilities reset his auto attack timer, so weave attacks between uses when going all in for maximum damage\n\n— DeClawd (@DeClawd) <a href="https://twitter.com/DeClawd/statuses/502167060596932609">August 20, 2014</a></blockquote>\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n</center>DeClawd''s tip focuses on sustained damage in trades and engages. By using your spells to reset autos and auto attacking in between each, you can get much more burst damage. Particularly early on in the laning phase, this can swing trades your way and push the enemy out of lane.\n\n<a href="/articles/lcs-pro-tips-elise" target="_blank">\n<img src="/sites/default/files/styles/full_width_scale/public/bf41595499_1.jpg?itok=ZpYTsISN" alt="" />\n</a>\n\n<strong>Vote for next week''s Pro Tip to help decide which pros will weigh in on <strong>Elise</strong>!</strong>\n\n<em>Katana is a Rioter in Esports who wishes that carrying from support was easier and that Thresh was never banned. You can follow her on Twitter <a href="http://www.twitter.com/riotkatana" target="_blank">@RiotKatana</a></em>\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li><a href="/articles/lcs-pro-tips-kogmaw">LCS Pro Tips: Kog''Maw</a></li>\n	<li><a href="/articles/lcs-pro-tips-lulu">LCS Pro Tips: Lulu</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'LCS Pro Tips: Renekton', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '55-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-09-29 11:21:03', '2014-09-29 11:21:03', '', 55, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=158', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
